  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony prosecution\n- Possible prison sentences\n- Significant monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of illegally obtained assets\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential civil forfeiture actions\n\n3. Legal Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Potential long-term imprisonment\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n\n4. Additional Potential Outcomes\n- Mandatory reporting to financial authorities\n- International legal complications\n- Potential extradition in some cases\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Jurisdiction\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific circumstances of the offense\n\nThese consequences can vary by country, but most developed legal systems treat money laundering as a serious financial crime.",
